parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering assist warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to steer
especially at low speeds
and the vehicle may make an abnormal noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump driver module can cause the engine to stall or not start, increasing the risk of a crash or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will crank but not start
the vehicle will stall while driving
the vehicle will hesitate to start
the vehicle will lose power while driving
the fuel pump relay will overheat and catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries while reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a black screen
upside-down image
or blue screen
or shows an error message
such as "Backup Camera Unavailable
Please Contact Your Dealership."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various issues, including loss of power, failure to start, or unexpected shutdown, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

messages appear on the console referring to updates needed
or the vehicle shuts down unexpectedly.
